    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-12-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-12-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="237"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d237">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Pruyn</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 86.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-12-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 14, 1864.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch of October 12, No. 62, has been
                    received, together with its voluminous appendix.</p>
                <p>The questions you have been obliged to consider, and the measures which you have
                    found it necessary to adopt in maintaining the treaty-guaranteed rights of the
                    United States in Japan, were very grave and important. The difficulties of the
                    case were greatly enhanced by the manifest need there was for intimate, cordial
                    and hearty co-operation between yourself and the representatives of the other
                    western powers. Having carefully examined the proceedings, I am authorized by
                    the President to assure you they are fully approved. * * *</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert H. Pruyn</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.,
                            &amp;c., Kanagawa.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
